<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-24T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-24T18:00:00-05:00" n="502" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/21577</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d502fn1">Similar telegram, on the same date, to the
                                    American Consuls at Tampico, Vera Cruz, and Guadalajara.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-24T18:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 24, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>663. Department has given following statement to press: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>The Department of State is informed that certain newspapers
                                        in Mexico are reproducing articles recently published in the
                                        United States to the effect that this Government is making
                                        preparations to cope with disturbances in the Tampico oil
                                        district and that American forces are held in readiness for
                                        that purpose. The Department of State desires to announce
                                        that there is no foundation whatever for the articles
                                        mentioned.</p>
                                </quote>
                            </p>
                            <p>Publish substance foregoing. Tampico, Vera Cruz, and Guadalajara
                                similarly instructed.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>